properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 17 at 2:55AM CST until February 18 at 12:00AM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
...SNOW AND A WINTRY MIX DEVELOPING TODAY...

* WHAT...Snow developing this afternoon, with a rain and snow mix
into the evening. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 4 inches.

* WHERE...Fond du Lac and Sheboygan Counties.

* WHEN...From noon today to midnight CST tonight.

* IMPACTS...Plan on deteriorating road conditions through the
afternoon with reduced visibility in falling snow. The hazardous
conditions will likely impact the afternoon and evening
commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The snow will likely be wet and heavy,
and will be difficult to shovel. Plan to allow extra time to
shovel your drive and walk.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM NOON TODAY TO MIDNIGHT CST TONIGHT
